Movie: Manila in the Claws of Light
Review: Attended a talk with the screenwriter (Sir Doy) and the actors that played Julio and Pol (Sir Bembol and Sir Tommy). Didn’t realize they were going to screen it. So I rewatched this sitting on a plastic chair and with the projection not properly fit for the screen. Screening pet peeve unleashed.. Even so, it was an experience watching this back home. A little heartbreaking tbh. There aren’t a lot of interviews with the actors / screenwriter available online either so…

The Unbearable Weight of Massive Talent

Review: This was a plane watch and that is exactly what it felt like

I enjoyed this. So many specific choices that can either make you laugh or fly right over your head and that’s what gives the film a nuanced viewing experience. The context of OFWs is not necessary but it does give this so many layers imo (at least while watching Abigail and her arc). I saw a little bit of someone I knew with every character - maybe that’s good or bad - i think it’s funny. the social critique is there if that’s the only thing you want to focus on but so is the thing that enriches the human experience.
